text.tspan: An image recipe defines how to create an sd-card-image
and the software-packages that should be installed:
sca-base-image: packages/configs common for all images
A buildconfig defines how to build for a specific platform (board/soc),
which bootloader and kernel to use, etc.
Every image and corresponding SDK can be build with each buildconfig.
For each image a SDK can be populated containing the
installed in the image. But the SDK is platform-specific
and therefore a SDK for a specific image has to be
build with every buildconfig in use.
